</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<POST>
<POSTER> Tony &lt;TonyJ1...@aol.com&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-09-12T13:42:00 </POSTDATE>
Virtually every Wednesday (though not today as I'm pressed for time
before work), I make the trek that many others do:  to the comic book
store (which these days, seems less like a comic store than a place
for gamers, but that's another story).  When I get my pulled comics, I
always peruse the shelves, just in case there's a book I forgot to
pick up, or there's a hidden title that I'd been meaning to get.  Once
I've made my purchases (I know my comic shop loves me, as I spend more
than $100 on new comics a month), I go sit in my car and read.  I turn
the car on to get a little AC, then crank the music down very low and
get lost in the weeks' stash.  Last week, while reading the latest
issue of Countdown, I started wondering where everyone else on here
reads their comics?
In the car?
In the study?
In the living room?
On the toilet?
At the office?
In the bed?

Tony
