On my way home from work, I stop at the LCS, which is only about 3/4
of a mile from my house. Usually, I get to the LCS before they've
finished pulling books for folders, so they just hand me mine instead
of putting it in my folder. Before I check out, I peruse the wall for
anything else new that piques my interest (or that I haven't put on my
pull list).

My LCS looks more like a headshop than a gaming store. The guy who
runs it is in a local band, so he has lots of music memorabilia, indy
CDs, DVDs, etc., but still mostly comics... and actions figures.

Before going home, I stop at the *other* LCS (local coffee shop and
*not* a Starbucks :P), which is right around the corner from my house.
I sit in my usual corner of the patio and read while drinking my iced
coffee and listening to the Michael Baisden talk radio show.
